observations.recommendation:
We recommended and Management agreed to:

Require the Municipal Treasurer to prepare a duly certified list showing the names of the taxpayers and the amount due and collectible for the year which data should come from the RPTAR or Taxpayer’s Index Card;

Furnish the Municipal Accountant a copy of the certified list to serve as the basis in recording the RPT Receivable and SET Receivable accounts in the books; 

Require the Municipal Accountant to set-up the RPT/SET Receivables in full amount based on the Certified List furnished by the Municipal Treasurer and not only on LGU’s share on RPT and SET income; and

Lastly, require the accounting office to record collections of Special Education Tax Income in the books of accounts it pertains.

Management to establish responsibility center for GFPS under the Office of the Mayor;

The MA provide Responsibility Center code in the SLs for the manual accounting; and

The MBO to provide RC code in the eBudget or (Budget if manual).

We recommended and Management agreed that:

The Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to secure pertinent records of the donated construction and heavy equipment from the Provincial Government of Zamboanga del Norte to determine the book value that will be used in recording the assets and Prior Period Adjustments accounts in the books;

Conversely, if securing of the pertinent records is not feasible, as an alternative, to conduct appraisal of the assets to determine the amount to be used in recording;

Demand from the Provincial Government of Zamboanga del Norte based on the Release order dated June 28, 2022, the turn-over of the two units that include the Service Utility Vehicle- Ford Ranger White (Chassis No. (VIN#)-MNCDMFF20FW431934) and the Transit Mixer- Fuso 10 Wheelers, A-1 Reconditioned Cowl -Yellow, Body- Green (Chassis No. FY515JX-510003) for immediate recording;

Facilitate the transfer of Certificate of Registration of the donated equipment under the name of the Municipal Government of Sibuco; and 

Submit the SP Resolution authorizing then Provincial Governor to donate the one unit of dump truck and the SB Resolution authorizing the Municipal Mayor to accept the nine units of equipment to the COA.

1. Establish proper coordination between the Bids and Awards Committee, Municipal Engineering, Budget and Municipal Development Offices regarding of the preparation of the report on the PPAs implemented and to be implemented by the municipality;

2. Require the concerned office to submit at the beginning of the year, the list of all on-going projects and those that are to be implemented during the year in accordance with the provision of 2.1 of COA Circular No. 2013-004 dated January 30, 2013;

3. Require the concerned office to conduct regular monitoring of all on-going projects implemented by the municipality and prepare monthly accomplishment reports as to its status of implementation and submit regularly Quarterly Accomplishment Report following the format in Annex B of the COA Circular No. 2013-004 dated January 30, 2013 to COA Office; and 

